Whereas the Taiwan Relations Act has been instrumental in maintaining peace, security, and
			 stability in the Taiwan Strait since its enactment in 1979, and it is in
			 the political, international and economic interests of the United States;

Whereas the Taiwan Relations Act also states that it is the policy of the United States to preserve and promote extensive, close, and friendly
			 commercial, cultural and other relations between the people on Taiwan, as
			 well as the people on the China mainland;

Whereas the United States is the third largest trading partner and the largest investor in Taiwan,
			 while Taiwan is the eleventh largest trading partner of the United States
			 and the sixth largest United States agricultural market;

Whereas Taiwan’s democracy has deepened with the second peaceful transfer of power from one
			 political party to another after the Presidential election in March 2008;
